caption: Love this place. A must if you are in the area.
Worst place ever the cashier is rude  the spanish girl on the Waffle iron is rude. I dont like this place and dont reccomend it.
This is a new favorite of mine. Absolutely love this place. Waffles were delicious and the staff super friendly.
Food is amazing. ESPECIALLY for the price. Definitely recommend. In addition, the african american lady that works there is sooo{ hospitable. Very loving and warming vibes there.
Dropped in on Tues. Really nothing but good experiences here. The bill was well within reason for the quality.
I wish there were more places like this around town. Quick and friendly service. It has a good atmosphere. I see why this place has a lot of positive reviews.
Wicked club was awesome.  Got extra meat and I'm still full 5 hours later.

I was very disappointed by my experience here. I am following a low FODMAP diet, under the guidance of a nutritionist and an therefore limited in what I can eat. I had done research ahead of time and thought this would be an inclusive option for someone with dietary restrictions.  When I walked in, a woman behind the counter listed off many ingredients they had run out of. I was able to adjust my order and waited to put it in. As soon as I said "gluten free" to the woman at the register, she rolled her eyes and started yelling at the first woman for not telling me they didn't have any. She wouldn't even tell me directly. I couldn't believe how rude the entire experience was.

Waffle could have been way better , my waffle bacon ,egg, cheese sandwich was poorly put together , sandwich was truly not worth me getting up early for Eggs not throughly cooked  , cheese barely melted , bacon thrown in  . A waste
Very rude staff

Efficient, friendly, and delicious. I LOVE this restaurant. I appreciate their gluten free options (which you would never be able to tell are gluten free, they’re that good)! I take out of town visitors here because it’s such a fun experience. Highly recommend!
It was ok. Service was disorganized and the workers were overwhelmed. Order came out to $24 for 2 people.
I'm sure it's generally good but I was given 2 waffles which were not fresh and killed the taste. Might try again
They open and close whenever they want to. Disappointing.
Grilled cheese waffle isn't worth writing home about, but they do have great gluten free options.
If your ever in DC this place is a must best waffles hands down
Excellent food, challenging service.

The staff was very rude and it seem like they went out of there way to make our food bad compared to what I have seen.. you would think in these times with places shutting down left and right that customer service would be a priority
The fried chicken and waffle was DELICIOUS.  Not too heavy AND they have sugar free syrup. 😉
Recommend the chicken and waffle with the sriracha honey. Chicken was a little thin and lacked a satisfying crunch.
Delicious food 😊

This is a small sized location and its seating is outside, the food is average but the waffles are disappointing. They're very crispy and more like a potato chip than an actual fluffy breakfast waffle. The breaded chicken was not satisfying as the actual breading did not stay on the chicken. The service was fine, it was nice to dine outside but the birds were very aggressive trying to get to the food. Overall we would not revisit.

Where I'm from we have this placed called Funk n Waffles and when I googled breakfast spots, I was thrilled at wicked waffle's menu.  Great chicken and waffles starts with the batter. Whatever batter they use for the chicken is amazing! I liked that it was breast instead of wings. Can't wait to come back to DC to try 1 of the sweet waffles!
One of the best sandwich shops in all of DC. They have an amazing menu selections and the service here is top notch.
Never again. Turkey bacon undercooked, not actual fried chicken and waffle was dry. Didn’t receive enough syrup to even cover my waffle or chicken and it came with a side of lettuce...

Ok the service is not the best but the food was "Da Bomb". Worth the trip.  During Covid-19 sitting arrangements is a bit awkward.  I had the French Toast Waffle with a la cart eggs and sausage, my friend had the cinnamon apple waffle .....DELICIOUS!!!
That chicken and waffles was the truth...great place and excellent customer service 💪🏾💪🏾

Will definitely visit again! Got a gluten free sausage egg plate and it was delicious, didn’t crumble apart, I could even eat it as a sandwich if I wanted. Workers were kind and orderly and handled crowds well. Menu was very clearly marked and there was no sense of a gf diet being a bother to cater do. Will DEFINITELY be returning to try the savory and sweet waffles!
Hello, I ordered a lot and the food is great. The service is even better!! Thanks
Delicious food and wonderful smells. Once in a lifetime opportunity
The Best sandwich shop in all of DC hands down. Wish there's one in L.A. They would go crazy for this place.
Great sweet and savory options!

Unique restaurant serving both savory and sweet waffles and waffle sandwiches. The smoked salmon waffle sandwich had a satisfying crunch and was pretty tasty. Others with me were also pleased with their meals. Beware that the space is tiny and the counter help was cold and unhelpful.
Came for the gluten free options - such good food!!!
I wasn't ever really a waffle person, but these were amazing customer service is always top notch here. They're light and crisp and even good when plain.

This place is wicked!!! So glad the reviews led me here. Otherwise there is no way for a tourist like me to find this place off the beaten path.  Take note that the venue is not big and there are only about 10 seats in there. However scores of people visit this place for obvious reasons.  Their waffles are really light and tastes awesome. The savory menu creative! Peking Duck Waffles, how can you resist trying this! This looks simply amazing but the meat is a little too sweet for me.  The simple savory waffles like egg and bacon plus Nutella waffles are absolutely brilliant. I dun muss bread at all!
Wicked
Best waffles. Great service. No fuss.

Holy smokes! The chicken and waffle us amazing! My son absolutely enjoyed the Nutella and banana waffles. Small place with loads of personality. Linda is an absolute delight, what a beautiful greeting. A must in DC

I'm generally not a huge fan of waffles, but this 70s vibe restaurant proved that I hadn't eaten a waffle until now. Let's just say wicked good is an understatement. I had "The Works" waffle, gluten free, for a classic breakfast take. No syrup needed. They cater to all your gluten free, vegan, lactose free, and organic needs. The waffles speak for themselves at what I rate a five star joint.

Me and my family got to wicked waffle at 1:40 and the staff said they were close, but online the time says 2pm. When trying to ask the staff about the hours of operation they ignored me. The staff was rude will never go back again.
The waffles were delicious but there were very puffy, I would love to have a thicker one or a couple on ones instead of just one then I would say It worth the price:(. People from Fl :)

Not fulling, light, I guess it's healthier.  It can be messy, because the waffle doesn't hold.  The place is tiny and packed, so you just have to get what you want and be out.  The Nova was better than my grilled chicken.  It's great to try once, if you are from out of town.
Good not zabihah doe but maybe next year
Very busy, but a rare find to have something open on Sunday in DC. Fast service, but the waffles are not thick and fluffy or really waffles in general.
Chicken and french toast waffle is as good as going back to bed after hitting the snooze bar.

Waffles were tasty. My son has gluten and dairy allergies and they have a gluten-free vegan waffle that he loved. The place is tiny.. very few places to sit. We ended up sitting outside even though it was cold and windy.
Thos place could do better. Food is fast and tastes good but the place seems a little neglected in terms of furniture and service. Would come back though

I had the strangest item on the menu, which is usually my thing.  The best items can be found this way.  I had the Hoisin duck waffle sandwich.  It was delicious!  Wife had GF waffle, she was very impressed.  Excellent food!
This place was amazing. Long Line but it moved quickly and was worth the wait. One of our favorite meals when we were in DC as it was cheap and delicious.
Great food with some unique twists on old favorites.
Great place to grab a bite to eat in DC.

Love this hole in the wall type shop, we stopped in for a brunch/late breakfast and couldn't believe how many options there were for waffles! You can even add on fruits and other sauces too if you're feeling extra hungry but overall a delicious stop that must be hand if you're in the area! I wish it wasn't so cold out so we can eat outside, since the sitting area is small if you're a larger group, but we still made it work!!! I'm drooling just thinking about these waffles and what all my friends got as well!!!
Waffles are too thin and don't hold up very well. Not do they taste like waffles. The taste is good, just super messy. Sorry no photos. But I had the grilled chicken and chipotle ranch.
Wonderful fast.  And Delicious.  Reccomend  chicken and waffles  but add a little hot sauce..

What an amazing place for us gluten free people! The gluten free waffles are absoluteley amazing. Crunchy in texture and not gumny or chewy like a lot of GF products. I had a sweet waffle with chocolate drizzle. It was so good I had to to for seconds and had a waffle with strawberries. So good! Customer service was outstanding,  everyone is so friendly. They also offer vegan waffles and almond milk.

This place not only makes awesome yummy waffles - their customer service is outstanding. The lady at the register is super nice and made our visit a fantastic experience. My wife is gluten free and the waffles are so good - she ordered a second one. 😆 Highly recommend this place!

Extremely rude staff and argued with us over multiple things. Don’t waste your time or hard earned money on this hole in the wall. Whole places smelled of a burned waffle because there was a smoking waffle just laying on the ground.
Straightforward waffles (sweet or savoury) - good and friendly service! A nice and hidden gem in downtown.
Food is amazing, and the service tops it!
Unique place to eat in DC. Got the chicken and waffles
Delicious food and extremely friendly service! I would definitely recommend this place.
Good and fast service

Small place, about 8ish tables outside, a cold December morning and we joyously ate out waffles outside. They were that good. I admit, I had my doubts walking up to this tiny place, which we picked out by it being the only resyurant with folks sitting outside- every table full. We had the fried chicken waffle and the strawberry cheesecake waffle. Seriously the best waffles in texture, lightness, crispiness, taste, size, etc. Add in the special flavors and we were debating after we finished if we should share one more order. Highly recommend! Oh and the folks there are super friendly!
Nice little spot with awesome waffles. I will definitely be going back for the Fuji apple and cinnamon waffle.
The food was amazing!
The line was outside the door and they barely had any seating. The food was pretty good though, need 1.5 or 2 waffles if you want to be full!
So good!! Service is funny.
One of my favorite places to eat in the area- just watch out for the hours, they’re a little wonky
Pleasant surprise, our intended spot was overcrowded, but this was an great alternative.
Delicious food.
Small place with a long line but it was worth the wait. Food was great but don't expect to have a place to sit indoors in the winter. Good on the go meal just make sure you got time to wait!

Wonderful cozy spot for light fluffy waffles.  I have been to this reaturant multiple times and each time, I have experienced friendly service and great waffles.  Options range between sweet and savory and I have been able to try waffles from both.  On the savoury side: the egg and cheese waffles sandwich is great, well prepared eggs and veggies nestled in a waffles that has a crispy exterior and airy interior. Another item in the menu you cant go wrong with is the grilled cheese to which you can add veggies.  On the sweeter side you have the perfectly prepared sweet waffles to which you can and should add a scope of ice cream and sweet drizzles. The classic PB and J sandwich is given a slight twist with the use of waffles as bread and after having it, that is now the only way I would enjoy it moving forward. Finally the star of the sweet menu is the cheesecake waffle, a large waffles covered in cheesecake pieces and batter accompanied by fresh strawberries and heaps of whipped cream.  Overall, the entire family has enjoyed going to this resturant. Constantly friendly service and great offerings.
Awesome food!! Great service and the food was so good I couldn't choose just 1.
Solid place, lots of gluten free options I always order a lot of food
3rd time going here. Waffles here are like clouds. Delicious!
My favorite item was the chicken salad and the dessert. Mmm I loved that we could bring our dog and that they took the time to come outside with some water and BACON for him!!

Wicked Waffle is absolutely delicious, I love how the waffles are light and don’t weigh you down, the service is wonderful, very friendly, especially Ms. Linda, she’s super sweet and provides excellent customer service to me. In my opinion, this spot is a Gem.
Not wheelchair accessible. I was extremely disappointed that they weren't real waffles. Food was not tasty.

What a wicked find for local cuisine! I had never before tried a breakfast sandwich with waffles in place of the buns, but I was not disappointed. The staff is kind, prices reasonable, and coffee excellent. It's a bit of a walk from the Mall, but it takes you right past the White House. 10/10, would eat again.

Very kind and hospitable staff and tasty sandwiches with waffles replacing the bread! I got the pulled pork sandwich, which was tasty, but the meat was so moist that my waffle was soggy before I even took the first bite. It was hard to hold together. If you go here and plan on ordering a hot sandwich that has the potential to soak through the waffle, get them to separate it from the waffle and then combine as you go. I'd like to try more on the menu!

I really enjoyed this waffle in DC. I have wanted to try it for a while it's always packed when I go by - so I go on the busiest holiday weekend.  I waited in line for about 15 minutes before it was my turn to order. I wanted to try a little bit of each so I chose the fried chicken waffle, with a side of bacon and eggs.  The waffle is just as delicious as they say you really don't need syrup but I chose to use it a  nyways. This was probably one of the most light and airy Belgian waffles I have ever eaten in my life. The fried chicken was pretty good, not amazing but Definately good.  Even though it looks busy at typically doesn't take people very long to eat and the Warriors are out quick. Would definately go back I enjoyed chatting with the people who work there. My goal is to up my belgian waffle game after eating here.  They offer a discount for Military, Police, EMS, and Firefighters; I think this is a super cool way for a business to thank first responders and public servants.
Lousy waffles

We stopped in for breakfast after a early morning appointment in DC. We were a party of two. The place had several dinners already eating at the small counters and outside. The store is designed to keep traffic moving. Enter one door and exit the other. We ordered two breakfast items (see photos). They were ok, not heavenly. Staff was positive. Well retun to check out a nutella or strawberry waffle.
Amazing food with Amazing customer service!!!  We will Definitely be back!!

We enjoyed our Nutella and chicken waffles. Very little indoor seating but there are places to sit outside. A decent cup of coffee would have received a 5-star review. OJ was fresh squeezed. Employees making our breakfast were very friendly and even singing while making our food. We would go back.

The staff was very nice and the food was excellent. I got the smoked turkey and French brie savory waffle. My husband got the grilled turkey croque monsieur with added ham. Both were full of taste with fresh ingredients. We definitely enjoyed our lunch there. There are a few seats inside and the air conditioning was great on the hot day.
The BLT waffle sandwich with avocado is the best!
I Love the waffle sandwiches.
Great food I recommend stopping and have a waffle they are wonderful. Very light and taste great
all ingredients were cold
Excellent waffles, fast service, and reasonable prices! A must visit and right near the Farragut West station. Ordered the chocolate waffle and it was a delight
Fried Chicken Waffle was amazing. The line was long for a reason.
Good food and service.... They Don't like the Dallas Cowboys.... Funny... Well one of them do... He cool with me.
Overpriced. And waffles sucked.
It's ok

I dont really do breakfast but I had to be at the VA early morning and had time to kill. The lady at the register was so sweet and even asked if I was military for a discount. To add to the great experiencen the eggs and waffles were the best Ive ever had.
Didn't eat there but the people are friendly and it is always crowded so it's a good sign.
Eh!
This place is nice for Sunday early morning breakfast. Little busy from the morning, but you can wait. Crispy baked waffles and, yes, bacons!! What a delight for starting of the weekend day!!

Are you effing kidding me? Wow. Best waffe ever. I had the mango and brie. Sophie and Cheri had bananas and strawberries, with and without Nutella. Yum.  Very cheerful, funny woman taking or order.  Tiny place.
Light, delicious waffles, even the gluten-free!
Fun place with great staff
It is Soo good it should be wicked good. You should try it out✅💯😍
Great waffles, best yet I promise!

My mom and I stumbled on this place while vacationing in D.C. We were very glad we did! It’s super close to the Club Quarters hotel on 17th Street (where we were staying). Great prices, good service, sidewalk dining, waffles so fluffy I barely needed to cut them, and crispy bacon. What more could you want? Many, if not all of the waffles can also be gluten-free if you desire. Hope we can come back next time we’re in town!
Yummy gluten- free savory waffle sandwich
(Translated by Google) Chicken patty and messy atmosphere like fried fried 5 hours ago  (Original) 5시간전에 튀겨놓은거 같은 맛의 치킨패티와 지저분한 분위기
Best waffles ever!
Super tasty. The turkey club was delish. Great change of pace from normal lunch places. I would say it's a must try in DC.
Delish!! And gluten free for those with Celiac sensitivity.
What’s not to love about waffles? Lots of fun combinations at a reasonable price although not much seating. Quick and friendly service
So glad we found this place!!! Got a Nutella and banana. Quick service and friendly staff. The waffle wasnt super doughy, which I liked. Overall impressed with it and would go back.
Delicious! So glad they had a gluten free option. They have basic combinations as well as fancier waffles.
Very good food and friendly service.
Excellent food
Great prices, great food. Peking duck was great, my favorite. Coffee was great
Pretty underwhelming. I paid $8 for the works waffle and felt very hungry afterwards.
1 waffle the size of 2 eggo waffles with 2 toppings is about $8. but tasted fine. minimal seating. terrible coffee.
Affordable for the area, great selection, fast service!! Delicious idea!
Tasteful.  But light. Order extra
Only bad thing i can possibly say is the line and limited space makes dining here challenging. Decent prices for DC too.
Yummy.  Tasty.  Must go here.

I had the gluten-free Nutella strawberry waffle, and it was heaven. Heaven! We arrived before 10 (on a Saturday), so the queue was short, the wait to get the waffles was brief, and there was table space available.
Incredible waffles for anytime

Wow. Those waffles are something else, and that's coming from a guy who loves waffle house.  So the dishes are interesting but maybe expected. Instead of bread for your sandwhich Classics like the club, or salmon which normally get bread for the sandwich get the  waffle treatment. And that's just the savory The sweet waffles like "The Works" are supremely sweet and you have to be prepared for it.  To try both sweet and savory you are looking close to $20 for two items but I'm telling you you wont regret it. But they mentioned you can have a police/military discount, so I'm sure that can help. The line can be long though so unless you are prepared to wait up to 30 minutes to get a delectable waffle or waffle sandwhich, look somewhere else.  In short definitely recommend if you have never had something like this.

My friends and I got a few waffles here. The fried chicken waffle was underwhelming. The fried chicken was precooked and reheated. So the chicken was tough and not juicy. The fried breading was well seasoned though. And the best part was the waffle.  The smoked Turkey and brie waffle was all right. The cabbage and tomato was fresh, but the turkey was simply cold cut and didn't add much flavor.  I think waffle sandwich is a novelty idea but that's all it is. And probably not worth waiting 20-30 mins in line.
Wow waffles, great service, note worthy experience. Must try is seasonal veggie and humus and fresh orange juice
Liked it!
French toast waffle is off the chart make sure you get 2 you don't want to share.
Great food, friendly staff, and an inexpensive meal. The waffles were light and fluffy.
Outstanding and creative sandwich
Great food
I was looking up for the best waffles in DC this morning. Wicked waffles was among them. I had turkey melt and Nutella with strawberries... Both were delicious!

Delicious food with great service and an inexpensive menu. Definitely a recommended visit if you're in the DC area.  It's a small establishment with outdoor patio and a few bar seats along the windows. We will go back again to try everything on the menu!
Light and delicious. Perfect for breakfast in the summer. Military and LEO discount as well.
I am a huge waffle fan. I got the grilled cheese waffle with tomato and bacon (which was under $10!!) the waffle was great, crispy but not crunchy. I will be getting it again.
Fantastic Waffles, priced right.

For what it is this place is great. The staff is very friendly! It's a small restaurant that offers out door seating. Your food gets done very quickly and the waffle I had was great. It was light and fluffy and very well presented.
Good options for waffles and at affordable prices
Delicious. Had the strawberry and banana waffle. Waffles were light and fluffy. Exactly what you would want in a waffle. Staff were friendly. Place to sit and eat outside.

Stumbled in this little gem on an early sunday morning with my daughter.  Everything waffle you can think of from savory to sweet. Just look at the pics!  The waffles are really light and fluffy! So good!  Not a huge dine-in space, but for the taste and the price, I would definitely go back!
Delicious
Neat little place.  Waffles were great,service was fantastic, and it really is on the cheaper side for the location.
Absolutely fantastic turkey sandwich. Great break from the expected.
Awesome chicken and waffles and very friendly service! Most places around here lack service so that was very refreshing! Nice outdoor seating.
If you’re looking for a regular brunch spot, this is NOT it!!! This place was amazing! Definitely hit the spot!
Gluten free airy and delicious waffles. Most items are gluten free and they have a dedicated waffle maker. Make sure to tell them you are ordering GF.
Waffles are to die for
Fantastic place really great food fast service

Disappointing in every way... Greasy, chewy panko chicken. One extremely soggy waffle. One extremely brittle and dry waffle (Can’t even “do bad” consistently). Didn’t make my waffle fresh, just threw pre-made ones on a heating tray for a couple minutes.  I recommend giving this a hard pass.

Was in DC from Florida and was determined to try Wicked Waffle before I went back. Had the taxi stop in front and grabbed the chicken and waffles and the Nutella waffle to eat while I was waiting at the airport.  These waffles are HEAVENLY!!!! A must try if you are in DC !!!!

Try this place!  Brilliant eatery concept...order a hand-crafted sandwich made on a thin waffle (instead of bread or a wrap).  Why didn't anyone else think of this???  Seating inside and outside, and great service.
Catering order- chicken was sub standard and for the price we paid, not enough waffles. The fruit bowl was good.
Best dang waffles ever!!!!!

The service was fast, friendly, and the waffles were the best I've ever had in the states.  Light, crispy, airy!!  Its usually heavy and game-like everywhere else but this was geather light and like a dream.  Perfectly complimentary with either savory or sweet toppings.  Will definitely come again when I next have the chance!!
Very delicious and good price, I would definitely come back again.
Very good and fast! The lady at the register was very positive and happy to have us as customers, will definitely return.
Good food. A bit expensive for what you get.
This was an interesting restaurant's ir was all based on waffle sandwiches so if you want to replace your bread with a waffle this is the place to go.
The location in DC has the best staff in town. Check them out...Their food is awesome also!!!!!
Really good waffles with a ton of options. Prices aren't bad either!
Delicious, amazingly crafted waffles.
Went back a second day and they sold out of food an hour before they closed. Kind people, fast service, good prices and delicious food.
Crispy chicken and yummy waffles!
The service is great. Really fast and the lady at the cashier greets you with a warm smile. Food is solid too.
A great place with a great idea. its the price of a full size meal though for comfort food, something to consider.
Outstanding food and staff! Do yourself a favor and try it!
Discovered this place 5 years ago and it is a must have every time I go to DC! I love the variety of toppings and the many ways to have one of those delicious wicked waffles!
This is my favorite place to eat in D.C.! Gluten free options are amazing! A must-try!

(Translated by Google) I ate salmon waffles but it was very delicious. It was easy to eat because it was cut into three. It was lined up, but was able to order quickly as soon as it turned. There are few seats, but there is no problem because there is a park nearby.  (Original) サーモンワッフルを食べたがとても美味しい。三つに切ってあって食べやすかった。並んでいたが回転早くすぐに注文できた。席数が少ないが近くに公園もあるので問題なし。
The waffles are amazing! Has a mom and pop feel and the staff is so friendly and charismatic. You can have something sweet or salty. I love this place!
Quick and delicious. Could come back every day to try something new! Big hit with the kids.
Stopped to get a to-go order. Staff seemed more concerned with having personal conversations than with getting my order right. My waffle club was missing the most important part - no bacon :(
Food takes a while to order but the chicken and waffles with Sriracha Syrup is so good
This was awesome for breakfast!!

This place is just fantastic. My daughter and I were looking for someplace to grab a bite to eat and just happened to find Wicked Waffle. From the lady who took our order to the great guys that prepared our waffles, everything was awesome. We are so glad we found this great place to eat. Thanks so much.

Really interest place, I came in for a quick grab after sightseeing town with my friends and it was a delight to find quite a good variety on waffles. from Savory to sweet tooth tastes.  I like the menu combinations if only I wish the price was more accessible. Looking forward for my next visit.  Make sure you try the Salmon option Waffle, fresh and Delicious

We were so happy with our wicked waffle experience!! The food was excellent! We had a big order because we wanted to try a variety. They were super nice about it! We weren’t sure about the fried chicken and waffles but wanted to give them a try. They were our favorite!! The sweet ladies working there threw in an extra order of chicken and waffles at no charge with a smiley face on the container that said thank you!! They were super kind and made us feel welcome. We loved it so much we went back the next day, in the poring rain! It was worth it!! One of our favorite places to eat while vacationing in DC!!

The best waffle I have ever eaten - don't get the waffle French toast; just get a waffle with some yummy toppings, like the Nutella & banana. It was so good that we canceled our breakfast plans to visit here a second time.
The food was cold and not that great. Very disappointed!
Definitely order on of the waffle sandwiches rather than an open face. The sandwiches were not as big as I expected them to be. It's a small shop with little indoor seating.
Absolutely tasty!!

Great food. Very interesting and new ideas. There was very little indoor seating so it was a little difficult in cold weather but they had plenty of outdoor space. Love the staff! Friendly funny and so polite!
It is good. If I had anything bad it is the chicken with the waffles are shrinking.  Maybe I caught them on a busy bad day. They are crowed for a reason
Unique and tasty waffles!  The staff is well organized and friendly. A pleasant breakfast.
i loved wicked waffles it was wicked

The food wasn't very good. I got the waffle with pork and my partner got the French toast waffle. The French toast was soggy. The pork was pretty average. The coffee was cold and the place is small. Overall it's pretty dirty outside and in, and seating isn't plentiful. I would not go back. I'm not sure how this place has so many positive reviews.
Very tasty food. The restaurant was super packed when we arrived. The cooks worked quickly to build everyone's meals and were friendly.
Great food. Dining room is limited though
Delicious chicken and waffles! The waffles are light and crisp, the panko breaded chicken perfect...I will be back!
Great food!  Chicken and waffles on point

Amazing place to stop and grab a bite. The food is delicious, the staff if welcoming and nice. From the moment you walk in they make you feel welcomed and at home. While here I witnessed the workers offer free meals to members of the local police force. Top notch quality food and people here. Highly recommend. 😍😍😍
Soooooo Gooodd

Cute little place. I got coffee and a bacon, egg, and cheddar waffle sandwich. Both were delicious. The waffles were crispy and yummy. Food was ready quickly and service was good. Will be back next time we’re in town!
Delicious light and airy waffles. Had the sweet waffle with caramel and my hubby had the French toast waffle. Both were delicious!
Wickedly Wonderful
Go check them out

Come here for dessert waffles, the savory ones are good but not worth paying a premium to have ordinary ingredients between two waffles. I ordered the chicken and waffles which would have been good had the waffle not been so hard that I had to saw at it with my knife. I visited Washington D.C. with my girlfriend this past Summer, and oddly enough, the main desire behind the visit--at least for me--was to find a great chicken and waffle restaurant. Living near Atlanta, there is an abundance of chicken and waffle establishments, however, the availability in terms of walking distance and public transportation can make getting there somewhat of a hassle--unless you're willing to rough it through Atlanta traffic. A nice juxtaposition is the Metro in D.C.--providing excellent accessibility to a conveniently placed chicken and waffle joint; aptly named "Wicked Waffle." Worried that we wouldn't make it in time, we were pleasantly surprised that they were open when we did arrive. Although the setup of the restaurant is somewhat eccentric, the staff and the food were beyond appealing. As the adjective insinuates, the "Wicked" describes "Wicked Waffle's" nontraditional approach to preparing Chicken and Waffles. There were a variety of off-the-wall menu items and my girlfriend and I were impressed by the quality within each of our differentiated choices. My initial thought was that I would need syrup or some other condiment to accent my order--however, as I delved into the dish, I quickly realized that the Chicken had been carefully glazed with a plethora of sweet and savory juices that accented the dish perfectly.  With all this said, "Wicked Waffle" will absolutely be on the agenda when we visit D.C. again.

I just knew I would be getting a warm, soft waffle with a nice tender of fried chicken on it. Instead, I got a cold pre-prepared waffle with a soggy, unidentifiable piece of chicken on top. I did not enjoy it at all.  Today, I ordered a grilled cheese waffle and again, got just that. I'm confused as to how the cheese got melted but the waffle is still hard and room-temperature. Gave them a second chance, won't be back.

My disappointment is mainly due to the fact that I read an article about gluten-free places in DC and had a different idea of what it would be. This is a TINY fast food joint. I ordered the Memphis Style pork waffle gluten free and the PB &J gluten free. I sure wish the menu would have indicated that the pork comes with barbecue sauce on it because I could've asked for my sandwich without it. The pork sandwich was so awkward to eat that I ended up taking the waffles off and eating the meat with a fork.  The PB&J was excellent. When I ordered the Pork sandwich gluten free, the cashier spent a few moments studying the menu as if she didn't believe me that it's one of the gluten free options. And of course, the one dish I was really hoping to find gluten free is not; fried chicken and waffles.
